title: JUI-P’ Sajjad Ullah wins PK-32 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Jamiat-Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI-P) candidate Sajjad Ullah has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-32, Kohistan Lower by securing 13,826 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was independent candidate Khan Member who bagged 12,496 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 54.68 per cent.
